    "plan_content": "Here's my complete implementation plan:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `Bun.INI` Public Namespace\n\n### Background\n\nThe codebase has a well-established pattern for format namespaces. Each one has: a `*Object.zig` file with `create()`/`parse()`/`stringify()` → exported in `api.zig` → registered as a lazy property in `BunObject.zig` (3 places) → typed in `bun.d.ts`. The existing internal `src/ini.zig` is NOT used (it's `.npmrc`-specific with env-var substitution).\n\n### Files (5 total):\n\n| File | Action |\n|---|---|\n| `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig` | **CREATE** — self-contained parser + stringifier |\n| `src/bun.js/api.zig` | **MODIFY** — add `pub const INIObject = @import(...)` |\n| `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` | **MODIFY** — 4 additions in 4 locations |\n| `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts` | **MODIFY** — add `namespace INI` with parse + stringify |\n| `test/js/bun/ini/ini-public.test.ts` | **CREATE** — public API tests |\n\n### `INIObject.zig` design:\n\n**`parse()`** — iterates lines directly to build `JSValue` objects:\n- Skip blank lines and `;`/`#` comment lines\n- `[section]` / `[foo.bar]` → traverse/create nested JS objects by splitting on `.`, set `current_section` \n- `key = value` → parse value (bool/null/number/quoted-string/plain-string) and `putMayBeIndex` on current section\n\n**`stringify()`** — walks JS object with `JSPropertyIterator`:\n- Scalar top-level props first: `key = value\\n`\n- Object top-level props as: `\\n[section]\\nkey = value\\n`\n- Arrays as: `key[] = v1\\nkey[] = v2\\n`\n- Nested sub-objects: dot-notation keys\n\n### `BunObject.zig` changes (4 spots):\n1. `pub const INI = toJSLazyPropertyCallback(Bun.getINIObject);` (~line 70)\n2. `@export(&BunObject.INI, .{ .name = lazyPropertyCallbackName(\"INI\") });` (~line 140)\n3. `pub fn getINIObject(globalThis, _) JSValue { return INIObject.create(globalThis); }` (~line 1289)\n4. `const INIObject = bun.api.INIObject;` (~line 2083)",
